text: Bonellitia scobina is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cancellariidae, the nutmeg snails. ==Distribution== This type of sea snail was documented in the eastern shore of Australia, more specifically in the South-East region around Sydney. ==References== Category:Cancellariidae Category:Gastropods described in 1906
title: Bonellitia scobina
